Test Plan – Login Functionality

1. Introduction

This test plan describes the testing strategy and scope for verifying the login functionality of the Practice Test Automation website.

The goal of this testing effort is to ensure that the login system works correctly, securely, and provides appropriate feedback to users.

2. Application Under Test

Website: https://practicetestautomation.com/practice-test-login/

Module tested:

Login functionality

3. Objectives

The objectives of this testing are:

Verify successful login with valid credentials

Verify login failure with invalid credentials

Validate proper error messages

Verify correct redirection after login

Ensure input fields behave as expected

4. Scope of Testing
In Scope

Username and password validation

Login button functionality

Error messages

Successful login behavior

Logout functionality

Out of Scope

Performance testing

Security testing

Database validation

Cross-browser compatibility

5. Test Strategy

The login functionality will be tested using manual testing techniques.

Testing will include:

Positive testing (valid credentials)

Negative testing (invalid credentials)

Boundary testing (empty fields)

UI behavior validation

Test cases will be designed based on the login workflow and expected user behavior.

6. Test Environment

Testing will be performed using:

Web browser: Google Chrome

Operating System: Windows

Internet connection

7. Entry Criteria

Testing will start when:

The login page is accessible

The application is stable and responsive

8. Exit Criteria

Testing will be completed when:

All planned test cases are executed

Any identified issues are documented

9. Deliverables

The following documents will be produced during the testing process:

Test Plan

Test Scenarios

Test Cases

Bug Reports

Test Checklist

10. Risks

Potential risks include:

Test environment instability

Changes to the website during testing

